In the MATTER OF Agnes S. WLADYKA, An Attorney At Law (Attorney No. 032741994) D-93 September Term 2018
082546 Supreme Court of New Jersey. April 18, 2019

ORDER

This matter have been duly presented pursuant to Rule 1:20-10(b), following a granting of a motion for discipline by consent in DRB 18-354 of Agnes S. Wladyka of Mountainside, who was admitted to the bar of this State in 1994;

And the Office of Attorney Ethics and respondent having signed a stipulation of discipline by consent in which it was agreed that respondent violated RPC 1.1(a) (gross neglect); RPC 1.5(b) (failure to set forth in writing the rate or basis of a legal fee); and RPC 1.15(d) and Rule 1:21-6(a)(2)(recordkeeping violations; attorney fees must be deposited in an attorney business account);

And the parties having agreed that respondent's conduct violated RPC 1.1(a), RPC 1.5(b), RPC 1.15(d), and Rule 1:21 -6(a)(2), and that said conduct warrants a reprimand or lesser discipline;

And the Disciplinary Review Board having determined that a reprimand is the appropriate discipline for respondent's unethical conduct and having granted the motion for discipline by consent in District Docket No. XIV-2016-0360;

And the Disciplinary Review Board having submitted the record of the proceedings to the Clerk of the Supreme Court for the entry of an order of discipline in accordance with Rule 1:20-16(e);

And good cause appearing;

It is ORDERED that Agnes S. Wladyka of Mountainside is hereby reprimanded; and it is further

ORDERED that the entire record of this matter be made a permanent part of respondent's file as an attorney at law of this State; and it is further

ORDERED that respondent reimburse the Disciplinary Oversight Committee for appropriate administrative costs and actual expenses incurred in the prosecution of this matter, as provided in Rule 1:20-17.
